rComments: I've had Prof. Cohen for 3 other courses in university and she's earned the top spot out of all profs I've had. She is very clear when outlining assignments and exams and it's because she actually cares about students' learning outcomes. She went as far as helping me on projects outside of school. Overall, she's extremely helpful and inspiring!

She is so nice and approachable; her lectures are interesting. There were a lot of assignments in this course, but she makes it very clear on how to proceed with him. Overall, she is an amazing prof and I hope to take more courses with her!
Really nice prof, made boring course content mildly interesting, cares about students, prepares you for future university courses, lots of assignments but no final
She knows what she's talking about (more often than not). Helpful and pleasant.

I loved Professor Cohen. I had her in CCT110 and liked her despite the course content being boring. Her course aims are simple and easy to understand. She always answers emails quickly and is there when you have questions. I think she is one of the best profs utm has. She cares about her students and keeps lectures interesting. Take her classes!!!!

Ms. Cohen is a very good teacher who knows a lot about what she is teaching. The only think I didn't like about her (this is pretty big) is that she tries to force her beliefs on you a bit too much. The course ends up being a semester - long campaign for grassroots initiatives (think Occupy Movement, hipster culture) and less about other Cs of P.
